<TITLE> Govt mulls keeping shops open after 8pm in Ramadan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 4 (bdnews24.com)The government may allow shops to run beyond 8pm during the Ramadan going by the demand of the businessmen, the commerce minister said on Tuesday. "The government is considering keeping shops open after 8pm," Faruq Khan told reporters after opening 'Accounting Science Week' of Dhaka University commerce faculty on the campus. Former state minister for power Shamsul Haque Tuku on July 30 said the government would not change the decision to keep shops closed after 8pm even in the Ramadan. Bangladesh Shop Owners' Association at a press briefing on Monday asked the government to revoke the decision. They said they were facing huge losses. Otherwise, the association said, the shop-keepers will disobey the government order and run business by lighting candles or lanterns. b
